  "text": "Temporal action localization The dominant method for detecting the temporal extent of actions involves sliding windows of several fixed lengths through the video, and classifying each video segment to determine whether it contains an action [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The segment classifier can be based on hand-engineered feature descriptors [CITATION_4] , trained CNNs [CITATION_5] , or a combination of the two [CITATION_6] . In contrast to this segment-based approach, we are able to detect actions of arbitrary length without sliding multiple windows through the video.",
